                                                                                                                       7                                      Stuart Broad eyes IPL III 
            THE DAILY TELEGRAPH                      
	Cape Town: Stuart Broad has taken the first step towards playing in next years Indian Premier League and possibly landing a $750,000 deal.         
	He turned down the chance to play in last years IPL, preferring to concentrate on preparing for the Ashes. But it was learnt that his representatives have made contact with Lalit Modi to begin the process of signing for one of the eight franchises.         
	Provided he gains clearance from the ECB, he will be added to the list of players on sale at the third IPL auction in Mumbai on Jan. 19 when one-year deals worth a maximum of $750,000 will be on offer.         
	England meet South Africa in the third ODI Friday.                                                                                                                     
